ons—DTLX and QLHV monitors plus the Agent Status check—all appear to be running based on their recent updated times, though there's a discrepancy with e7885813 showing an ended timestamp while remaining active.\n\nChecking against the baseline from 17:51 UTC, all three critical sessions are still running with no new failures or blockers, and the Telegram group is also still active. There's one minor discrepancy where the state file shows e7885813 as done at 17:34, but it's still running in the current state—this was already noted in previous reports, so it's not a new issue. The pipeline appears stable across all these checks.\n\nNow I'm verifying the exact timestamp for e7885813 to confirm whether this discrepancy was already documented. Looking at the DTLX monitor session `cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31`, it's still actively running with an updated timestamp of 1776190482806. The QLHV monitor session also appears to be running with an updatedAt of 1776190306699, and the Agent Status to Lead session is still active despite having an endedAt timestamp of 1776188076580.\n\nThe telegram group session for -5163901258 is running with an updatedAt of 1776189713169. Comparing the current state against the baseline from 17:51 UTC, all three cron sessions are still running—DTLX monitor, QLHV monitor, and Agent Status—with no new failures, blockers, or state transitions detected.\n\nThe main orchestrator session ending at 18:04 is a separate heartbeat session that completed normally, and the QLHV telegram direct session ending at 17:59 is also expected. There are no actual changes from the last stable baseline, so I'm staying silent on this.","thinkingSignature":"e7e9cbe7bd31d20f8554ef880e3a547791d7ee83e868d46f59722bd0837853e3"},{"type":"text","text":"Comparing current state (18:14 UTC) vs. stored baseline (17:51 UTC):\n\n**Baseline:** `cron:ed2d0b5d` ✅ `cron:6f3323ef` ✅ `cron:e7885813` ✅ | `telegram:group:-5163901258` ✅ | Pipeline HEALTHY\n\n**Current:**\n- `cron